task.summary: Default task
Minor changes to the authentication system.
Transparent interface migrated over from photon field.
Migrated SphericalProbabilityDistribution over from photon field into Common.
Migrated SphericalProbabilityDistribution over from photon field into Common.
Some improvements to chem package (towards spectrogram support). Introduced ResourceTranscoder and migrated some file decoding from SpatialData to individual transcoders.
Migrated Ply parsing to PlyResource.MeshReader.
Migrated Raw file decoding into RawResource.SceneReader.
Eliminated the need for persistence delegates when using XML encoding by establishing setters which did not previously exist.
Migrated electrodynamics classes and interfaces out of chem and into physics.

Introduced Electron and Spin which together describe an electron and all potential excitation energy levels. Electrons allows Electron instances to be grouped together so that excitation energy levels for a whole valence group can be calculated together.
Compute a Tensor of potential absorption energies for a set of electrons. Not all of these are valid, as some combinations may result in two electrons of the same spin occupying the same subshell.
Introduced compaction for producers. This allows the depth of a producer tree to be reduced by merging together producers, especially those that are associative or distributive.
This is version 0.3.
Starting version 0.4.

Introduced expect, which is used to determine whether a vector is an intersection point. The value returned by get() and the value returned by expect() for a given Intersectable are placed into a Relation and then the distance parameter for a Ray is solved for to perform intersection calculations.
Expanding the econ package.
More expansion of economics functionality.
Read and Write operations for ExpenseData. ClockSynchronizer now sleeps after synchronization rather than before.
Some improvements to physics data structures used in rendering and some new data structures for economics.
